Charles Czeisler, professor of sleep science at Harvard Medical School and specialist at Brigham Hospital and Women's Hospital, designed a course he believes to be the first of those species in the United States.
The idea of the course came after giving a speech about the effect of sleep deprivation on learning.
At the end of the class, a girl came to me and said, "Why did I know this only now, in my last year of college?"
