For the first time this year, the course explains to students how good sleep habits help academic and sports success and generally improve health.
Professor of Psychology at Harvard Medical School and Executive Director of Health Services Paul Barreira says the University decided to introduce a course after a serious lack of sleep was observed in students during the week.
The one-hour course consists of a series of interactive tasks.
One of these tasks includes a picture of a dormitory where students have to click on cups of coffee, curtains, tennis shoes and books to find out what the effects of caffeine and light are, how the lack of sleep affects success and how important sleep routine is.
