And now here comes a page from our Almanac on Sunday Morning: September 30, 1882, 136 years ago and several days ago ...the day of the birth of future physicist Johannes Wilhelm "Hans" Geiger in Germany.
Geiger developed a method of detecting and measuring radioactivity, and from this invention later developed a device known as the Geiger counter.
