According to FWC, the conditions of heterogeneous alga bloom are reported in the Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Charlotte and Collier districts, indicating a reduction in concentration.
The red tide stretches about 130 miles along the coast from the northern part of Pinellas County to the south of Lee County.
Areas of flowering can be found about 10 miles from the shore of Hillsborough County, but in smaller places than last week.
The red tide was also spotted in Pasco County.
